    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 123–Bennington/1:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander of United States Naval Forces in the Eastern
                        Mediterranean</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Admiral <persName type="to">W. S.
                            Benson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-26">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 26, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Adriatic 38. Naval committee reconvened today. Conditions reached a stage where
                    all the committee except the Italian Admiral <pb facs="0431" n="343"
                        xml:id="pg_343"/> wished to call persons who could tell of conditions
                    preceding and during the occupation of Fiume, so as to form correct idea of
                    actual existing conditions. Italian Admiral Mola insisted his instructions would
                    not permit this and requested time to consult his Government. This means more
                    delay but agreed to in interests of harmony.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
